track_notes: Off trail wear pants views are good road to TH past wood chute requires high clearance and when wet maybe 4wd only
This drive needs 4WD. Also, during rainy season, it can get very muddy. check the weather for recent rain. I recommend a 4WD with high clearance, wench would be good in case of recovery.

See my map for the Drive to this point! Need high clearance vehicle - watch for muddy season. Once parked this is a bush-whack (no defined trail) up to the ridge. Once on the ridge there seems to be a rocky trail that will lead you to the summit. Once on the summit, it is a breath-taking view of Prescott Valley, Prescott National Forrest, and looking to the east you can see the red-rock of Sedona.
